    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 1: DHHC8 specifically binds and palmitoylates GRIP1 (pulldowns for various mutants in HEK293T cells).\n\nFigure 2a,b: synaptic localization of DHHC8 was shown by co-localization with Bassoon (BSN) in immunofluorescence imaging of primary hippocampal neurons.\n\nFigure 2c: in biochemical fractions, DHHC8 was enriched in PSD fractions.\n\nFigure 2g,h: DHHC8 Palmitoylated GRIP1 in primary neurons.. Experimental description: mice were used in these experiments, although not explicitly mentioned. To confirm mouse protein sequence annotation is valid, M&M confirms that the HA-tagged sequences were from mouse; \"HA-tagged mouse DHHC5 and DHHC8 and mycHis-tagged human DHHC8 cDNA have been previously described (Fukata et al, 2004; Ohno et al., 2006).\"\n\nantibody:\nDHHC5 (Sigma), ZDHHC8 (Everest Biotech)\n\nshRNA knockdown:\nshRNAs (in vector pLKO; Mission shRNA library) targeting sequences identical in both rat and mouse DHHC5 (5'-CCTCAGATGATTCCAAGAGAT-3') or DHHC8 (5'-CTTCAGTATGGCTACCTTCAT-3') were tested for their ability to reduce expression of HA-tagged DHHC5 and DHHC8 mouse cDNAs in cotransfected HEK293T cells.",
